The Tennessee swimming and diving team completed the third day of competition at the SEC Championships in Fayetteville Ark PERIOD Wednesday PERIOD The Vols top honor for the day was a second place finish in the  medley relay PERIOD Tennessee fell to sixth place with a total of  points PERIOD UT currently trails Alabama  Georgia  Florida  Auburn  and first place Kentucky  PERIOD

Todays competition started with the final diving event of the championships the platform competition PERIOD Tennessees Jake Dorsey and Phillip Jones had to step up and dive in place of injured teammate Sal Vilardo PERIOD Dorsey finished eleventh with . points while Jones placed sixteenth PERIOD

The swimming portion of the SEC Championships got underway with the  medley relay and  freestyle relay PERIOD The team of Matt Parrish Justin Hoggatt Jeremy McDonnell and Renato Gueraldi finished second with their fastest time of the year just twohundredths of a second behind Florida PERIOD In the  freestyle relay the Vols team of Brett Tannhauser Greg Simpson George du Rand and Andrew Bree took home a fourth place finish in a time of . pERIOD

The swimming championships continue on Thursday with the  freestyle  individual medley  freestyle and the  freestyle relay PERIOD The preliminaries start at  a.m. with the finals beginning at  p.m PERIOD

The University of Tennessee womens swimming and diving team continued competition at the  Southeastern Conference Swimming and Diving Championships on Wednesday at the Arkansas Natatorium PERIOD The highlights of Wednesdays action were the first two swimming events and the final diving event of the week PERIOD

Junior Stacy Binyon made the first final of her career in the womens platform diving competition after finishing sixth in the preliminaries with a score of . pERIOD In the finals Binyon tallied a total of . to take seventh place and score key points for the Lady Vols PERIOD

 Tennessee diving coach Dave Parrington said PERIOD 

To kick off the swimming events the Lady Vols finished eighth in the 200y medley relay in a seasonbest time of . pERIOD The squad of senior Bianca Jones junior Nicole Brannock junior Bethany Hall and junior Sara Wingfield finished fourth in their heat to take eighth overall PERIOD Auburn took the 200y medley crown with a time of . pERIOD

In the evenings final event the 800y freestyle relay Tennessee finished ninth with a time of . from the team of Wingfield freshman Livia Trevisan senior Elizabeth Philp and senior Valerie Conte PERIOD Georgia won the event with a poolrecord time of . pERIOD

In the team standings the Lady Vols are in fifth with  points after five events PERIOD LSU leads after three strong days of diving with a score of . while Alabama is in second with  and South Carolina is third with a total of . pERIOD

The Lady Vols will continue with the fourth day of the SEC Championships on Thursday PERIOD The preliminaries are slated for a  a.m PERIOD CT start with the 500y freestyle 200y individual medley 50y freestyle and the 200y freestyle relay PERIOD The finals for all of those events will begin at  p.m PERIOD CT with a 35minute break before the last event PERIOD
